Current used car market trends in Bangalore as per CARS24’s internal data

Petrol stands out as the dominant fuel in Bangalore.

As per CARS24’s internal data, used petrol cars continue to hold a strong 71% share in the market for used cars in Bangalore in 2024, with no change from 2023, remaining the go-to for affordable city driving. Second hand Diesel cars see a modest 1% rise, reinforcing their appeal for longer commutes and highway travel. Used CNG car adoption remains negligible, largely due to limited pump infrastructure.

For used cars in Bangalore, manual gearboxes continue to be the first choice

As per CARS24’s internal data, used manual cars in Bangalore dominate the landscape, making up 84% of listings with a slight 1% decline year-on-year. Used automatic cars account for 16% and are growing, reflecting drivers’ slow but steady rising preference for easier commuting in traffic-heavy conditions.

The used car market in Bangalore is still driven by old hatchbacks.

As per CARS24’s internal data, used hatchbacks continue to lead with a 58% share in the market for 2nd hand cars in Bangalore, though down by 2% from 2023. Used SUVs are gaining ground with a 4% rise, signalling a growing preference for road-ready, elevated drives. Sedans maintain a steady 22%, indicating consistent demand for comfort-oriented options.
